.TH "iio_buffer_read_outer" 9 "iio_buffer_read_outer" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
iio_buffer_read_outer \- chrdev read for buffer access
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "ssize_t" iio_buffer_read_outer
.BI "(struct file *filp "  ","
.BI "char __user *buf "  ","
.BI "size_t n "  ","
.BI "loff_t *f_ps "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "filp" 12
File structure pointer for the char device
.IP "buf" 12
Destination buffer for iio buffer read
.IP "n" 12
First n bytes to read
.IP "f_ps" 12
Long offset provided by the user as a seek position
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function relies on all buffer implementations having an
iio_buffer as their first element.
.SH "RETURN"
negative values corresponding to error codes or ret != 0
for ending the reading activity
